Package: causalontology
Type: Package
Title: R Binding of the Causalontology Standard
Version: 4.0.0
Authors@R: person("AI University (AIU)", email = "ai.university.aiu@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The R binding of the Causalontology standard (specification
    4.0.0, adding the attitude, predicted_occurrence, and prediction_error
    kinds, semantics Rules 24 and 25, and the widened assertion
    about-reference, over the folded-in 3.0.0 delta of the ordinal tick
    unit, the cross_stratal_seam kind with Algorithm F, and the conduit
    realized_by reference): content-addressed identity over RFC 8785 (JSON
    Canonicalization Scheme) identity-bearing bytes with SHA-256, Ed25519
    record-level signing and verification (RFC 8032), validation against the
    twenty-one specification JSON Schemas (including cross-file schema
    references), the semantic rules and the five normative algorithms of
    Section 12 (bridge closure, bridged hierarchy reachability, stratal
    classification, the skip decision procedure, and unit normalization)
    plus the rule 13-25 helpers (bridge, conduit, and cross-stratal-seam
    well-formedness and the seam home rule, state value and unit coherence,
    covering-law and retrocausality checks, the prediction-to-observation
    pairing, and graph acyclicity), and an in-memory conformant store with
    idempotent immutable puts, signed add-only provenance records with
    quarantine, materialized enrichment views with contributors, retraction
    and succession lineage, the resolve minimum, the deterministic
    cycle-breaking view rule, and the stigmergy gap read. Conformance is
    defined by the 137 vectors (V01-V137) frozen at specification 4.0.0; run
    conformance.R against them. Crypto uses a pure-R SHA-256 plus the 'openssl' package
    for Ed25519 (RFC 8032).
